   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Leo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(i) Financial inclusion: the project will help broaden access to credit for low income populations that could not have formal access to credit otherwise.  Bringing these under-served populations into the formal banking system has the following benefits: i) better cost of credit compared to informal money lenders; ii) customer protection through the regulatory framework, and iii) a credit history useful for future credit requests.  (ii) Housing Improvement and Education: about 50% of the loans granted by ABIL are used for home improvement and education. In a post-apartheid context, improved housing and education are critical for South Africa, as they contribute to the integration and empowerment of previously disadvantaged populations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This Summary of Investment Information relates to a potential equity investment in African Bank Investment Limited (ABIL, the Company). The investment is intended to strengthen the Companys capital base in order to grow its lending operations. African Bank Limited (ABL), a wholly own subsidiary of ABIL, is an existing client of IFC.</narrative>
  </description>
